# Evergreen A1 Marketing — Cursor Rules
# Drop into every client project root as .cursorrules

## STACK
- Next.js App Router, Tailwind CSS, Vercel, GitHub
- Images: next/image always, WebP, lazy load below fold, fetchpriority=high for hero
- Icons: Lucide React
- Schema: /lib/structured-data.ts — always import from here

## NEVER DO
- No plain <img> — always next/image
- No hardcoded colors outside tailwind.config.js
- No page without metadata (title + description)
- No inline styles except dynamic values
- No console.log in production
- No raw JSON-LD inline — always use /lib/structured-data.ts
- No component that breaks at 320px

## SEO — EVERY PAGE
- Title: 50-60 chars, keyword FIRST
- Meta description: 150-160 chars with CTA
- Canonical URL + Open Graph tags
- One H1 with primary keyword
- BreadcrumbList schema + HTML breadcrumbs
- LocalBusiness schema on every page + page-specific stacked
- 2+ CTAs, 3-4 internal links

## MOBILE — PRIORITY #1
- Test at 375px before done
- Sticky click-to-call: fixed bottom, mobile only, href="tel:+1XXXXXXXXXX"
- Touch targets: 48px minimum, 16px minimum body font
- Always set width + height on images (prevents CLS)
- No horizontal scroll

## CLIENT CONFIG — FILL IN
CLIENT_NAME=
CLIENT_PHONE=
CLIENT_PRIMARY_COLOR=
CLIENT_HEADING_FONT=
CLIENT_BODY_FONT=
CLIENT_PRIMARY_KEYWORD=
